# Figma-First Dashboard UI/UX Workflow

Use this rule when the user asks for dashboard UI/UX work, Figma sync, or design-to-code.
Companion: [[webapp-frontend]] patterns, [[frontend-route-contract]] routing.

## North star

Build the **full dashboard component library in Figma first** (net-new frames for every primary panel), get user approval per wave, then implement in vanilla JS/CSS on **https://127.0.0.1:8182** only.

Do **not** code from the Cover frame (node 1-25) alone — it is tokens only.

## Master prompt (copy for each run)

When starting a component wave, state:

1. **Goal** — one sentence (screen + job-to-be-done)
2. **Deliverable** — net-new Figma → approve → code (default for this rule)
3. **Figma file** — `FMWpss3fGm0yzbjiyP3wSx` (Old Logan Capital Design System)
4. **Target node** — existing frame URL or `"create frame: <Name> — Success"`
5. **Verify URL** — `https://127.0.0.1:8182/?screen=<mode>&section=<alias>`
6. **Scope** — section id(s), in/out of scope, success criteria

