## Figma MCP workflow (strict order)

### Phase 1 — Understand

1. Read `index.html` anchors, `panels/<name>.js`, `modules/router.js`, `readability.css`
2. Read `wiki/frontend-route-contract.md`
3. `get_metadata` on file `0:1` — confirm target frame exists

### Phase 2 — Figma (net-new default)

Load `/figma-use` before any `use_figma` write.

1. `search_design_system` — reuse `ol/*` variables and Components — Calibration (7-24)
2. `use_figma` — create frames for **all 5 states**; place on Design System page below prior waves
3. Annotate: API fields, DOM ids, pass/fail semantics
4. **Approval gate** — share node URLs; do not code until user approves wave
5. Optional: `generate_figma_design` capture from 8182 for parity; refine; delete capture layer

**If design already exists:**

- `get_design_context` + `get_screenshot` + `get_variable_defs` on target node
- `get_code_connect_map` (Javascript) if Org seat allows — else manual map to panel modules

### Phase 3 — Implement

- Adapt Figma output to vanilla ES modules (not React/Tailwind verbatim)
- Fix API/UI field mismatches when KPIs render empty
- Preserve `data_quality` and guardrail visibility
- New alias: `router.js` + `wiki/frontend-route-contract.md` + `tests/test_static_router.py`
- CSS only in `readability.css`

### Phase 4 — Verify

1. Browser MCP: `https://127.0.0.1:8182/?screen=<mode>&section=<alias>`
2. Expand ancestor `<details>`; exercise load/error/empty/retry
3. `python -m pytest -q` on touched tests
4. Report: Figma links, changed files, token map, QA checklist

## Reusable Figma primitives (extend in DS)

When building new panels, compose from:

- **KPI tile** — match `decision-gate-tile` / Components 7-24 (label, value, sub, pass border)
- **Summary strip** — gold muted text in disclosure `<summary>` (see calibrationSummaryStrip)
- **Reliability bar** — forest fill, gold 50% gate, ok/bad row border (calibration-reliability-*)
- **Ledger pills** — cream bg, rounded source counts (calibration-ledger-pill)
- **Health tile** — healthRibbon grid pattern
- **Disclosure card** — panel-disclosure + card system-quality-nested

## Output format (every delivery)

1. UX rationale (hierarchy, scan path, failure modes)
2. IA / state table
3. Token map (Figma ol/* → --ol-*)
4. Figma link(s) OR approval gate links
5. Verification (8182 screenshots + pytest)

## Session start checklist

When user says "next Figma wave" or pastes the master prompt:

1. Identify wave from matrix above (default: next incomplete wave after calibration)
2. State P-level, files to touch, validation commands
3. Run Phase 1–2 in Figma only unless user says "approved, implement"
4. One wave per session unless user explicitly requests parallel waves
